Program: The History Hour
Title: The 1968 Belgrade Student Revolt
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqlk
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 10 Jun 2018
The 1968 student revolt in Communist Yugoslavia, an assassination attempt that sparked Lebanon's war, Adolf Eichmann's execution, plus the sudden death of Nigeria's strong man in less than clear circumstances and 'from couch to 5k' that inspired a global running craze. (Photo: Sonja Licht with her fellow protester and later her husband, Milan Nikolic, at the site of the protests. Credit: Licht-Nikolic family archive) Show less